{"comments":"ProceduralEasing — Easing functions that cannot be represented as cubic beziers.\n\n## Why These Exist Separately\n\nCubic bezier easing curves are monotonic in the time dimension — they can\nonly move forward through time. This makes them unable to represent:\n\n- **Elastic**: Oscillating overshoot with decay (like a spring)\n- **Bounce**: Multiple impacts with decreasing amplitude\n\nThese easing functions require procedural evaluation at runtime.\n\n## Physical Models\n\n### Elastic\n\nModels a damped harmonic oscillator: ẍ + 2ζω₀ẋ + ω₀²x = 0\n\nWhere:\n- ω₀ = natural frequency (controls oscillation speed)\n- ζ = damping ratio (controls decay rate)\n\nFor underdamped systems (ζ < 1), the solution oscillates while decaying.\n\n### Bounce\n\nModels inelastic collisions with a surface. Each bounce:\n- Reverses velocity\n- Loses energy (coefficient of restitution < 1)\n- Occurs at progressively shorter intervals\n\n## Usage\n\nThese cannot be converted to CSS — use JavaScript/WebGPU runtime evaluation.\nThe data types here define the parameters; the runtime evaluates them.\n","declarations":[{"children":[],"comments":"Configuration for elastic (oscillating) easing\n\n## Parameters\n\n- **amplitude**: Peak overshoot magnitude. 1.0 = 100% overshoot.\n  Higher values create more dramatic oscillation.\n  Clamped to >= 1.0 (no negative or zero amplitude).\n\n- **period**: Time for one oscillation cycle, as fraction of total duration.\n  Smaller = faster oscillations. Default 0.3 creates ~3-4 visible bounces.\n  Clamped to > 0.\n\n## Mathematical Model\n\nFor ease-out elastic at time t ∈ [0, 1]:\n  y = amplitude × 2^(-10t) × sin((t - period/4) × (2π/period)) + 1\n\nThe 2^(-10t) term provides exponential decay, while sin() oscillates.\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["amplitude",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["period",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[111,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/ProceduralEasing.purs","start":[108,1]},"title":"ElasticConfig"},{"children":[],"comments":"Default elastic configuration\n\namplitude: 1.0 (no overshoot amplification)\nperiod: 0.3 (standard oscillation frequency)\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","ProceduralEasing"],"ElasticConfig"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[117,32],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/ProceduralEasing.purs","start":[117,1]},"title":"defaultElastic"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create elastic config with custom amplitude\n\nAmplitude is clamped to >= 1.0\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","ProceduralEasing"],"ElasticConfig"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[126,48],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/ProceduralEasing.purs","start":[126,1]},"title":"elasticWithAmplitude"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create elastic config with custom period\n\nPeriod is clamped to > 0\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","ProceduralEasing"],"ElasticConfig"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[135,45],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/ProceduralEasing.purs","start":[135,1]},"title":"elasticWithPeriod"},{"children":[],"comments":"Configuration for bounce easing\n\n## Parameters\n\n- **bounces**: Number of bounces. More bounces = more complexity.\n  Clamped to >= 1.\n\n- **restitution**: Coefficient of restitution (energy retained per bounce).\n  0.0 = perfectly inelastic (no bounce back)\n  1.0 = perfectly elastic (full bounce back)\n  Default 0.75 provides natural-looking decay.\n  Clamped to [0, 1].\n\n## Mathematical Model\n\nEach bounce follows a parabolic trajectory:\n  y = 4h × (t/T)(1 - t/T)\n\nWhere h = height (decreases by restitution^2 per bounce)\nand T = time for that bounce (decreases by restitution per bounce)\n","info":{"arguments":[],"declType":"typeSynonym","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Record"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["bounces",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Int"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":["restitution",{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"tag":"REmpty"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"RCons"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[168,4],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/ProceduralEasing.purs","start":[165,1]},"title":"BounceConfig"},{"children":[],"comments":"Default bounce configuration\n\nbounces: 4 (standard bounce animation)\nrestitution: 0.75 (natural energy decay)\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","ProceduralEasing"],"BounceConfig"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[174,30],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/ProceduralEasing.purs","start":[174,1]},"title":"defaultBounce"},{"children":[],"comments":"Create bounce config with custom restitution\n\nRestitution is clamped to [0, 1]\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Function"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Prim"],"Number"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"},{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","ProceduralEasing"],"BounceConfig"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}],"tag":"TypeApp"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[183,48],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/ProceduralEasing.purs","start":[183,1]},"title":"bounceWithRestitution"},{"children":[],"comments":"Elastic ease-in (oscillation at start)\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","ProceduralEasing"],"ProceduralEasing"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[238,34],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/ProceduralEasing.purs","start":[238,1]},"title":"easeInElastic"},{"children":[],"comments":"Elastic ease-out (oscillation at end, settling)\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","ProceduralEasing"],"ProceduralEasing"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[242,35],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/ProceduralEasing.purs","start":[242,1]},"title":"easeOutElastic"},{"children":[],"comments":"Elastic ease-in-out (oscillation at both ends)\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","ProceduralEasing"],"ProceduralEasing"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"}},"kind":null,"sourceSpan":{"end":[246,37],"name":"../../hydrogen/src/Hydrogen/Schema/Temporal/ProceduralEasing.purs","start":[246,1]},"title":"easeInOutElastic"},{"children":[],"comments":"Bounce ease-in (bouncing at start)\n","info":{"declType":"value","type":{"annotation":[],"contents":[["Hydrogen","Schema","Temporal","ProceduralEasing"],"ProceduralEasing"],"tag":"TypeConstructor"